  "title": "Add remaining shadcn components to apps/admin",
  "category": "frontend",
  "description": "Expand the admin app's component library with the core shadcn/ui components needed for the Panopticon dashboard.\n\n## Components to add\n\nRun `npx shadcn add` for each:\n- button\n- input\n- label\n- form (with react-hook-form)\n- dialog\n- dropdown-menu\n- select\n- toast / sonner\n- tooltip\n- separator\n- skeleton\n- progress\n- alert (not to be confused with hx-alert)\n\n## What to do\n\n1. Run shadcn CLI to add each component after helix-shadcn-init is complete\n2. Verify each component renders correctly in the admin app\n3. Check TypeScript types compile cleanly\n4. Ensure no conflicts with existing recharts or lucide-react usage\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- All listed components exist in `src/components/ui/`\n- No TypeScript errors\n- Admin app builds successfully\n- Components are importable from their paths",
